            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "That commit was driven by designing a redraw API that makes sense in regards to updating the screen/flushing the UI. I am not familiar enough with treesitter to tell if our highlighter's needs differ from that. I have tried to establish that multiple times before in https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/28101#issuecomment-2091057965 and https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/30696#issuecomment-2452887985 (but got no response).\n\nHaven't been able to reproduce so some steps seem to be missing. Presumably `flush = false` will avoid the error again but in that case `nvim__redraw` shouldn't call `ui_flush()` either. But I suppose this boolean index can also be resolved while keeping the flush, I'm still not sure what would be preferred.\n",
