            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "> That commit was driven by designing a redraw API that makes sense in regards to updating the screen/flushing the UI. I am not familiar enough with treesitter to tell if our highlighter's needs differ from that. I have tried to establish that multiple times before in [#28101 (comment)](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/28101#issuecomment-2091057965) and [#30696 (comment)](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/30696#issuecomment-2452887985) (but got no response).\n\nBy all accounts, it's not the highlighter but other treesitter plugins for which that change was breaking. (The foldexpr is required to reproduce this; I can't reproduce the error with just treesitter highlighting.)\n\nIt's unclear to me why, but it seems that this breaks injection parsing in some way.\n",
